# AgentFrame Consulting Prep — .gitignore
#
# Purpose: keep COPYRIGHTED case content out of GitHub. The system/shape/structure stays;
# the case bodies (and original PDFs) never get pushed. They DO ship in the zip handed to students.
#
# What stays in GitHub: the tracker (shows how cases work), the README, all skills, scaffolding.
# What's excluded: every case body in library/cases/ except the tracker + README.

# --- Copyrighted case content (NEVER push) ---
# Ignore everything in library/cases/ ...
library/cases/*
# ... but keep the structure-bearing, publishable files:
!library/cases/.gitkeep
!library/cases/README.md
!library/cases/case-tracker.EXAMPLE.md
#
# NOTE: the REAL case-tracker.md is intentionally NOT un-ignored. It indexes the full list of
# copyrighted cases (titles, firms, locators), so it stays local and ships in the student zip —
# only case-tracker.EXAMPLE.md (fictional rows) is public. Same pattern as master-cv.EXAMPLE.md.
#
# Also gitignored (ship in the zip, never on GitHub):
#   library/cases/markdown/   — the 275 converted per-case files
#   library/cases/originals/  — the source casebook PDFs

# --- Source files with real personal info (never push) ---
_source-do-not-ship/

# --- Secrets (NEVER push) ---
.env

# --- The student case bundle (copyrighted content; hand out separately, NEVER push) ---
mccp-case-bundle.zip
*-case-bundle.zip

# --- Scratch / stress-test artifacts ---
_stress-test/
# node_modules IS vendored (pure-JS docx-js, no native binaries) so .docx generation works out of the box.

# --- Build / cache cruft ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# --- OS / editor noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.obsidian/
